In 1889 the part of the parish of Stamford Baron St. Martin in 
    Stamford Municipal Borough was transferred from Northamptonshire to the Parts of Kesteven, 
    while the rural part became part of the Soke of Peterborough. In 1894 the rural 
    part became the separate parish of St. Martin Without, after which Stamford 
    Baron St. Martin was wholly in Parts of Kesteven. Abolished 1.10.1930 and added to the parish of Stamford.
